# On Windows and MacOSX, the default is to ignore the SIGINT
# generated by a Ctrl-C on the keyboard.  This is a feature of
# the underlying C runtime: on Windows SIGINT is ignored by
# default because Ctrl-C is used by the GUI to signal to an
# app that it should gracefully shut down.  On MacOSX SIGINT
# is ignored by default because people can't remember whether
# Command-C goes to the app or the shell.
